{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "26", "m": "06", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "10", "M": "41", "S": "20"}}, "news": [{"title": "Nagpur civic body revives Kachipura eviction drive, 56 commercial units to get 15-day notice", "para": "Nagpur Municipal Corporation is set to resume action against 56 illegal commercial establishments on land leased to Dr. Panjabrao Deshmukh Krishi Vidyapeeth. Following a state government order vacating a decade-old stay, notices will be issued, giving occupants 15 days to remove unauthorized structures. The move targets businesses like restaurants and banquet halls, with no current plans to demolish the adjoining Kachipura slum.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/nagpur-municipal-corporation-resumes-kachipura-eviction-of-56-illegal-commercial-units/132008868?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-321700/132008868.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "Patna civic body's tax collections rise after first ARV revision", "para": "Patna Municipal Corporation has boosted property tax revenue by increasing the Annual Rental Value by 15%, the first revision in 30 years. This move, effective June 24, 2026, aims to fund infrastructure improvements.  A 5% rebate on lump-sum payments by June 30 for FY 2026-27 is also driving higher collections, with daily receipts surging significantly.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/patna-civic-bodys-tax-collections-rise-after-first-arv-revision/132008840?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-698868/132008840.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}, {"title": "Launched on May 14, Jharkhand's building regularisation portal gets 4,000 applications", "para": "Jharkhand's ambitious building regularisation drive is off to a slow start, with only 4,000 applications received since its May 14 launch. Confusion over rules, particularly the 25-foot road width requirement, is deterring homeowners. Many are urging the government to extend the July 13 deadline and clarify regulations, while also demanding a change to the plot size limit. Officials promise further examination and clarification.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/jharkhand-building-regularisation-portal-sees-only-4000-applications-since-launch/132008819?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-544306/132008819.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}]}